Operator :  Operator is a symbol which is used to inform what kind of operation needs to be performed on operands


Types of Operators:
1. Assignment =
2. Arithmetic 
3. Logical
4. Comparision
		>, <, >=, <= , ==, !=
		===(Strict Equal)
		!== (Strict Not Equal)
5. Inc/dec
6. Ternary Operator :
		(condition) ? true : false

Conditional Statements:
1. if
2. if else
3. if else if
4. Nested if 
5. switch

Syntax:

	if(condition){
		Statements;
	}

Syntax:
	if (condition){
		Statements;
	}
	else{
		Statements;
	}

Syntax: if else if : 
	if(condition){
		Statements;
	}
	else if(condition){
		Statements;
	}
	.
	.
	else {
		Statements;
	}

Nested If :
	Syntax:	
		if (condition1){
		
			if(condition2)
			{
				Statements;
			}
			else{
				Statements;
			}
		}
		else{
			Statements;
		}


5. switch :
	switch(choice){
			
		case number/string:
			statements;
			break;
		.	
		.
		default:
			Statements;	
	}

